source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: text
---
Mount a btrfs image or block device read-only via FUSE

Usage: fuse [OPTIONS] <IMAGE> <MOUNTPOINT>

Arguments:
  <IMAGE>
          Path to the btrfs image file or block device

  <MOUNTPOINT>
          Mount point

Options:
  -f, --foreground
          Run in the foreground (do not daemonize)

      --allow-other
          Allow other users to access the mount

      --subvol <SUBVOL>
          Mount the named subvolume as the root of the FUSE filesystem.
          
          The path is interpreted relative to the filesystem root, e.g.
          `--subvol home/snapshots/2025-01-01`. Mutually exclusive with
          `--subvolid`.

      --subvolid <SUBVOLID>
          Mount the subvolume with this tree id.
          
          Use the value reported by `btrfs subvolume list`. Mutually exclusive
          with `--subvol`.

      --no-default-permissions
          Don't ask the kernel to enforce file mode/uid/gid permissions against
          the calling user.
          
          By default the FUSE mount uses `default_permissions` so a non-root
          mounter can't read root- owned files in the image — matching kernel
          btrfs semantics. Pass this flag to bypass that check, e.g. when
          inspecting an image whose stored ownership doesn't match your local
          UIDs.

      --cache-tree-blocks <CACHE_TREE_BLOCKS>
          Number of tree blocks to cache (~16 KiB each).
          
          Set to 1 to effectively disable; large values trade RAM for fewer disk
          reads on tree walks.
          
          [default: 4096]

      --cache-inodes <CACHE_INODES>
          Number of parsed inode items to cache
          
          [default: 4096]

      --cache-extent-maps <CACHE_EXTENT_MAPS>
          Number of per-inode extent maps to cache.
          
          Each map is one entry per `EXTENT_DATA` item in the file.
          
          [default: 1024]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
